Explanation:

1. Initialize arrays for integerPart, repeatingPart, and nonRepeatingPart with the same length as the input strings s and t.
2. Iterate through the arrays and compare the elements of s and t.
3. If any pair of elements doesn't match, return false.
4. If all elements match, return true.

This solution has a time complexity of O(n) because it iterates through the arrays once. The space complexity is O(n) because it uses arrays of size n. The energy implications are low because the algorithm doesn't require any additional energy consumption.

